str2: Canaanite, a Biblical and archaic name for Phoenician. From Chanaan; a Chanaanoean, or native of gentile Palestine.
A woman, wife, my lady. Probably from the base of ginomai; a woman; specially, a wife.
From, away from. A primary particle; 'off, ' i.e. Away, in various senses.
That, that one there, yonder. From ekei; that one (neuter) thing); often intensified by the article prefixed.
Neuter of a derivative of an apparently primary horos; a boundary-line, i.e. a frontier.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Feminine Singular
str2: To go out, come out. From ek and erchomai; to issue.

parse: Verb - Imperfect Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To cry aloud, shriek. A primary verb; properly, to 'croak' or scream, i.e. to call aloud.
Lord, master, sir; the Lord. From kuros; supreme in authority, i.e. controller; by implication, Master.
A son, descendent. Apparently a primary word; a 'son', used very widely of immediate, remote or figuratively, kinship.
David, King of Israel. Of Hebrew origin; Dabid, the Israelite king.

parse: Verb - Aorist Imperative Active - 2nd Person Singular
str2: To pity, have mercy on. From eleos; to compassionate.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Accusative 1st Person Singular
str2: I, the first-person pronoun. A primary pronoun of the first person I.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive 1st Person Singular
str2: I, the first-person pronoun. A primary pronoun of the first person I.
Apparently a primary word; a female child, or descendant.
Badly, evilly, wrongly. From kakos; badly.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Middle or Passive - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To be possessed, be under the power of an evil-spirit or demon. Middle voice from daimon; to be exercised by a d?Mon.
